comment:
* A data class representing a known Wi-Fi network.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: NETWORK_SOURCE_NEARBY_SELF
variables.comment: * Network is known by a nearby device with the same user account.

variables.name: NETWORK_SOURCE_CLOUD_SELF
variables.comment: * Network is known via cloud storage associated with this device's user account.

methods.name: private static void validate(@NetworkSource int networkSource, String ssid, @SecurityType Set<Integer> securityTypes, NetworkProviderInfo networkProviderInfo)
public int getNetworkSource()
methods.comment:
* Gets the indicated source of the known network.
     *
     * @return Returns the network source as defined by IntDef {@link NetworkSource}.

methods.name: public String getSsid()
methods.comment:
* Gets the SSID of the known network.
     *
     * @return Returns the SSID of the known network. Surrounded by double quotes if UTF-8.

methods.name: public Set<Integer> getSecurityTypes()
methods.comment:
* Gets the security types of the known network.
     *
     * @return Returns a set with security types supported by the known network.

methods.name: public NetworkProviderInfo getNetworkProviderInfo()
methods.comment:
* Gets the device information of the device providing connectivity.
     *
     * @return Returns the information of the device providing the known network. Can be null if the
     * network source is cloud or unknown.

methods.name: public Bundle getExtras()
methods.comment:
* Gets the extras Bundle.
     *
     * @return Returns a Bundle object.

public static KnownNetwork readFromParcel(@NonNull Parcel in)
